timing_null_c..._compatibility(25.10)    timing_null_c..._compatibility(25.10)

Name
       timing_null_collection_return_compatibility

Syntax
       timing_null_collection_return_compatibility

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Allows you to migrate previous release scripts to the new use model.

       When  the  global is set to true, the software returns "NA" values that
       are consistent with the previous release. The nil return values are re-
       turned as an empty collection. This allows the return value to be  used
       directly by collection iterators, such as foreach_in_collection.

       The  default  value  is false, which is consistent with the current re-
       lease.

       Note: This compatibility option may be removed  from  future  releases.
       You  should  update  your  scripts to the new use model to avoid future
       problems.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

